description: The Divine Tree is close to blossoming, and Madara declares that there is only 15 minutes left before everything comes to an end.
title: A Shinobi's Dream

description: Ten Tails is on the brink of its final transformation and begins to form a massive Tailed Beast Bomb.
title: Something to Fill the Hole

description: Team 7 is finally reunited when Naruto, Sakura and Sasuke join forces. Then the reanimated former Hokage arrive to add their strength to the counteroffensive.
title: Team 7, Assemble!

description: Kakashi holds on to the hope that Obito can return to being the young man that he remembers. But Obito has abandoned the present as well as the memories of his friends and will not try to stop the Infinite Tsukuyomi.
title: Kakashi vs. Obito

description: Part 1 of a special two-part extra edition! The townspeople are going about their daily business on the streets of the Leaf Village when someone suddenly appears and starts sending them flying!

input: The Directive to Take the Nine-Tails!

title: The Directive to Take the Nine-Tails!

description: Part 2 of a special two-part extra edition!  Lee and company rush over and encounter a strange man who is so strong that even Neji can't defeat him.
title: Naruto vs. Mecha Naruto

description: Pressed by Naruto, Obito remembers the time he, Kakashi, and Rin teamed up for the Chunin Exam and when he promised Rin that he would become Hokage.
title: I'm Always Watching

description: With the return of his Rinnegan, Madara summons the Gedo Statue, ensnares all the beasts instantly and goes on a mad rampage.
title: The Hidden Heart

description: Naruto loses Kurama during his battle against Madara and is near death. As Tsunade and the other Leaf Village shinobi watch in fear, they are reminded that Naruto has always been their symbol of hope, even when he was not with them…
title: The New Chunin Exams

description: The Hidden Leaf begin preparing for the Chunin Exams. Tsunade orders Kakashi to personally deliver an invitation to the Hidden Rain Village and, at the same time, gather intel.
title: The Chunin Exams Begin!

description: The Chunin Exams finally begin and the proctor for Round One is none other than Shikamaru!
title: The Three Questions

description: Shikamaru introduces another question to be answered within three minutes. Will Neji and his team be able to pass this round?
title: One Worthy as a Leader

description: The Second Exam finally begins! To pass this stage, each team must take possession of both the Heaven and Earth scrolls and make it to the designated site in the center of the Demon Desert within 72 hours.
title: Demon Desert Survival

description: Like Lee, Shira can only use taijutsu. Gaara recognizes Shira's taijutsu abilities and appoints him as personal taijutsu coach.
title: As a Taijutsu User

description: Kiba and his team are in pursuit of Hidden Grass Ninja who have stolen their scroll.
title: Unwavering Gutsiness

description: Witnessing Ajisai's proficiency with the Summoning Jutsu, Tenten recalls her training with Guy.
title: The Imprisoned Pair

description: Ino, Sakura and Choji trudge across the desert without any provisions. Ino and Sakura start arguing when a giant scorpion attacks.
title: The Place Where I Belong

description: Gaara confronts Fugi, the mastermind behind the assassination attempt on his life.
title: Hopes Entrusted to the Future

description: Madara has transformed into the Jinchuriki of the Ten Tails and appears before Kakashi.
title: The Two Mangekyo

description: Naruto is on the verge of dying. Sakura desperately tries to save him, but Naruto's heart gives out.
title: On the Brink of Death

description: With his father's teachings spurring him on, Guy sets out on his final battle.
title: Papa's Youth

description: It's been three years since Naruto set out to train with Jiraiya, and he's just returned to the Hidden Leaf Village.
title: The Ones Who Will Inherit

description: Konohamaru immediately begs Naruto to teach him a new jutsu and he starts to go over the basics...but his explanations are very vague.
title: Naruto's Rival

description: Naruto has been revived and has acquired the Six Paths power. He rushes in to help, and his battle against Madara begins.
title: To Rise Up

description: Madara now possesses the Rinnegan in both eyes, and he is the strongest, most despicable enemy the newly reunited Team 7 has ever faced.
title: The Infinite Dream

description: Madara activates the Infinite Tsukuyomi, and anyone exposed to the light of the full moon...
title: The Infinite Tsukuyomi

description: Tenten falls under the Infinite Tsukuyomi and wakes up in the Hidden Leaf Village.
title: To the Dream World

description: Tenten is relieved to see that she is not alone, but her relief is short-lived.
title: Where Tenten Belongs

description: The Akatsuki summoned the Ten Tails, but the Princess of Rappu Castle sealed it away safely.
title: Killer Bee Rappuden: Part 2

description: Killer Bee gets caught in the Infinite Tsukuyomi and begins dreaming.
title: Killer Bee Rappuden: Part 1

description: Karin is caught within the Infinite Tsukuyomi and dreams of her past.

input: To See That Smile, Just One More Time
See That Smile, Just One More Time
That Smile, Just One More Time

title: To See That Smile, Just One More Time

description: Tsunade has fallen into a dream state and awakens to find herself in the Leaf Village, where she discovers Jiraiya's final book, and begins to read.
title: The Loser Ninja
